It has always been of great interest to me how we can use branches to work with so many people at the same time, and achieve our goals faster.
One of the sentences that summed uo what I liked the most about this is "Another way to view a branch is to consider it an extremely long-lived database transaction that provides Snapshot Isolation.".
Moreover, I enjoyed reading more about how to automate this processes, and the use of hooks. I had only used hooks on react for state changes in web pages so seeing another type
for version control was interesting.
